            "content": "# Changelog\n\n## 2026-04-02 (commit 891024d)\n\nFix critical ELF loading bugs and harden the loader.\nTested on x86-64 and aarch64 with gcc 14, -Wall -Werror.\n\n### Critical bug fixes\n\n- RELA addend not used. x86-64/aarch64 use Elf64_Rela but code did\n  `*addr += load_bias` (REL-style implicit addend). Fixed with compile-time\n  `#if ELFW_DT_RELW == DT_RELA` dispatch: RELA uses\n  `*addr = load_bias + reloc->r_addend`, REL keeps `*addr += load_bias`.\n- ro_start used p_offset (file offset) instead of p_vaddr (virtual address)\n  for read-only bounds checking. Replaced single ro_load pointer with\n  find_load_segment() to correctly derive permissions from the PT_LOAD\n  that owns each relocation target.\n- ro_load dereferenced unconditionally. NULL crash if no read-only PT_LOAD\n  segment. Eliminated by replacing ro_load with per-relocation segment lookup.\n- mmap() return value unchecked. MAP_FAILED produced bogus load_bias. Added\n  checks on all mmap/mprotect calls with fail() on error.\n\n### High-priority bug fixes\n\n- open() return unchecked. fd=-1 fed into pread() silently. Now checked.\n- pread() return values unchecked. Partial reads left ehdr/phdr\n  uninitialized. Replaced with pread_exact() that requires full byte count.\n- get_dynamic_entry() returned ElfW(Word) (32-bit on 64-bit targets),\n  truncating 64-bit addresses. Changed to uintptr_t with d_un.d_ptr.\n- mprotect granted PROT_WRITE alone during RO relocation. Read-modify-write\n  needs read permission. Fixed to prot_from_phdr(target) | PROT_WRITE.\n- Hardcoded pagesize 0x1000. Fails on 16K/64K page systems. Changed to\n  sysconf(_SC_PAGESIZE).\n\n### Medium-priority bug fixes\n\n- Architecture validation accepted any of EM_X86_64/EM_ARM/EM_AARCH64\n  regardless of build target. Now validates e_machine, EI_CLASS, and\n  EI_DATA at compile time per target architecture.\n- Integer overflow in span calculation. Crafted p_vaddr + p_memsz could\n  wrap. Added add_uintptr_or